WEBVTT

00:09.076 --> 00:12.179
♪ <i>Okily‐dokily, okily‐dokily</i> ♪

00:12.246 --> 00:14.181
♪ <i>Come meet Ned Flanders</i> ♪

00:14.248 --> 00:16.583
♪ <i>And his two boys</i>
<i>Rod and Todd</i> ♪

00:16.650 --> 00:19.586
♪ <i>He's friends with God</i>
<i>and has a ripped bod</i> ♪

00:19.653 --> 00:22.089
♪ <i>Diddly</i> ♪

00:22.155 --> 00:24.625
♪ <i>Doodily, diddly</i> ♪

00:24.691 --> 00:27.294
♪ <i>Doodily</i> ♪

00:27.361 --> 00:32.599
♪ <i>Diddly...</i> ♪

00:32.666 --> 00:36.503
♪ <i>Doodily</i> ♪

00:36.570 --> 00:39.072
♪ <i>Diddly, doodily, diddly...</i> ♪

00:39.139 --> 00:41.174
No couch, boys.
I gave it to the poor.

00:41.241 --> 00:43.243
‐Yay!
‐Yay!

00:43.310 --> 00:45.078
♪ <i>A‐diddly‐doodily</i> ♪

00:45.145 --> 00:47.014
♪ <i>Diddly‐doodily.</i> ♪

00:49.016 --> 00:51.051
Neddy? Neddy.

00:51.118 --> 00:53.120
Oh, Maude, you've come back.

00:53.186 --> 00:55.789
Completely clothed
and untouchable.

00:55.856 --> 00:58.058
This is the sexiest dream
I've ever had.

00:58.125 --> 00:59.126
Wait, Maudie.

00:59.192 --> 01:00.727
Just one little kiss.

01:03.730 --> 01:05.666
(howls)

01:05.732 --> 01:07.234
All tongue, no lips.

01:07.301 --> 01:08.769
Just like Maude.

01:08.835 --> 01:09.937
(crying)

01:10.003 --> 01:11.772
Daddy, why are you crying?

01:11.838 --> 01:13.907
Oh, just watering
the old lip lawn.

01:13.974 --> 01:15.509
I had a dream about your mom.

01:15.576 --> 01:17.010
Don't you ever dream about her?

01:22.749 --> 01:25.485
Faster, Mommy, faster.

01:26.720 --> 01:27.654
Aah!

01:27.721 --> 01:29.089
Ow!

01:30.257 --> 01:31.458
(screams)

01:32.526 --> 01:34.061
What's wrong, Todd?

01:34.127 --> 01:37.130
I can never unsee that.

01:38.765 --> 01:40.367
(whimpers)

01:40.434 --> 01:42.569
It's okay, son.
Just a bad dream.

01:42.636 --> 01:44.071
Want some lukewarm water?

01:44.137 --> 01:47.975
Daddy, I can't remember
what Mommy looks like.

01:48.041 --> 01:50.143
I think I might have
a video or two of your mother.

01:50.210 --> 01:51.411
ROD:
What's wrong?

01:52.245 --> 01:53.480
(screams)

01:54.548 --> 01:57.417
I'm doing
Mommy's old skin routine.

01:57.484 --> 01:59.753
Now, that's the healthy way
to grieve.

01:59.820 --> 02:01.555
(Todd groans)

02:04.191 --> 02:06.193
<i>(humming "Deck the Halls")</i>

02:08.528 --> 02:09.963
<i>(giggles)</i>
<i>I'm scared.</i>

02:10.030 --> 02:13.033
<i>Well, I have faith in you.</i>

02:14.067 --> 02:15.369
<i>Who are you people,</i>

02:15.435 --> 02:17.237
<i>and what have you done</i>
<i>with my family?</i>

02:17.304 --> 02:18.872
<i>‐Answer me!</i>
<i>‐(chuckles)</i>

02:18.939 --> 02:22.009
<i>Oh, Dad, every time we make you</i>
<i>shovel the driveway,</i>

02:22.075 --> 02:24.144
<i>you wind up someplace crazy.</i>

02:24.211 --> 02:25.879
<i>Won't you join us for dinner?</i>

02:25.946 --> 02:27.514
<i>(chuckles):</i>
<i>He sure will.</i>

02:27.581 --> 02:29.583
<i>I'll pick him up tomorrow.</i>

02:30.617 --> 02:33.687
(crying):
Mommy was so nice.

02:33.754 --> 02:35.856
And she still is,
Roddily Doddily.

02:35.922 --> 02:38.392
How do you know?
Have you heard from her?

02:38.458 --> 02:40.360
Oh, uh, n‐no, sir.

02:40.427 --> 02:43.130
But, uh, faith is believing
in something without proof.

02:43.196 --> 02:45.632
Uh, you can't see my lip
below my mustache,

02:45.699 --> 02:48.035
‐but you know it's there.
‐Can I see it?

02:48.101 --> 02:49.369
No.

02:49.436 --> 02:51.238
My math teacher said

02:51.304 --> 02:54.141
believing in something
without proof is crazy.

02:54.207 --> 02:56.576
You think the coat
of many colors was crazy?

02:56.643 --> 02:58.812
Noah's ark and the Holy Ghost,
crazy?

02:58.879 --> 03:02.582
Don't tell me you're doubting
Balaam's talking ass.

03:03.950 --> 03:08.021
Mommy, if you still remember me,
give me a sign.

03:08.088 --> 03:09.623
<i>This is Homer Simpson</i>
<i>auditioning</i>

03:09.690 --> 03:12.192
<i>for the air guitar championship</i>
<i>of the world.</i>

03:12.259 --> 03:14.428
<i>I'm taking you down,</i>
<i>Bjorn Turoque.</i>

03:14.494 --> 03:16.496
<i>(imitating guitar playing)</i>

03:21.468 --> 03:23.403
♪ <i>Praise God from whom</i> ♪

03:23.470 --> 03:27.374
♪ <i>All blessings flow</i> ♪

03:27.441 --> 03:29.376
♪ <i>Praise God</i> ♪

03:29.443 --> 03:34.314
♪ <i>It's almost time to go</i> ♪

03:34.381 --> 03:36.983
♪ <i>This boring sermon</i> ♪

03:37.050 --> 03:41.188
♪ <i>Must end soon</i> ♪

03:41.254 --> 03:43.824
♪ <i>Arena football's</i> ♪

03:43.890 --> 03:47.461
♪ <i>On at noon.</i> ♪

03:47.527 --> 03:48.829
HOMER:
Ooh!

03:48.895 --> 03:50.530
<i>(crowd cheering)</i>

03:50.597 --> 03:51.698
Whoo‐hoo!

03:51.765 --> 03:55.102
And for that simple reason,
we are right

03:55.168 --> 03:58.672
and Episcopalians
are wrong, wrong, wrong.

03:58.739 --> 04:00.107
Now I'd like to invite

04:00.173 --> 04:02.409
our littlest parishioners
to the front.

04:02.476 --> 04:05.245
Gertie, a little
traveling music, please?

04:05.312 --> 04:08.448
(slow hymn playing)

04:10.517 --> 04:13.120
Soon as we can, we're
replacing her with Spotify.

04:13.186 --> 04:16.189
I'm taking middle C.

04:17.357 --> 04:18.825
So, tell me, young Christians,

04:18.892 --> 04:20.994
if you could speak
to Baby Jesus,

04:21.061 --> 04:22.329
what would you say?

04:22.395 --> 04:24.331
I'd say thank you
for being born,

04:24.397 --> 04:26.333
'cause that gave us Christmas.

04:26.399 --> 04:27.834
ALL:
Aw!

04:27.901 --> 04:29.269
Mmm, I'm killing it.

04:29.336 --> 04:31.171
Ralph, what would you say?

04:31.238 --> 04:32.939
I'd say, "Baby Jesus,

04:33.006 --> 04:35.942
thank you for dying
for our shins."

04:36.009 --> 04:38.311
(congregation chuckles)

04:38.378 --> 04:41.214
And you, Todd?
What would you say?

04:46.153 --> 04:49.856
(hoarsely):
I lost my voice from crying.

04:49.923 --> 04:51.525
Oh, come on, young man.

04:51.591 --> 04:53.260
You're my closer.

04:53.326 --> 04:55.162
("Charge" playing)

04:56.596 --> 04:58.865
What would you say to Jesus?

04:58.932 --> 05:00.634
I'd say...

05:00.700 --> 05:02.302
thanks for nothing!

05:02.369 --> 05:04.805
My mommy's dead
and she's never coming back,

05:04.871 --> 05:06.973
and I don't believe
in God anymore.

05:07.040 --> 05:08.141
(feedback screeches)

05:08.208 --> 05:09.609
(congregation gasps)

05:10.710 --> 05:13.713
No. No!
(whimpers)

05:17.250 --> 05:19.052
Thank God these
collection baskets were empty.

05:19.119 --> 05:20.453
You're welcome.

05:25.125 --> 05:28.195
♪ <i>A mighty problem is our Todd</i> ♪

05:28.261 --> 05:30.864
♪ <i>His faith in God</i> ♪

05:30.931 --> 05:34.401
♪ <i>Is failing</i> ♪

05:34.467 --> 05:40.173
♪ <i>Homer accidentally killed</i>
<i>his mom</i> ♪

05:40.240 --> 05:46.112
♪ <i>He knocked her</i>
<i>off a railing.</i> ♪

05:52.285 --> 05:53.887
Now, son,
let me put this gently.

05:53.954 --> 05:55.722
We're all going to hell!

05:55.789 --> 05:59.059
You opened a doorway
to disbelief in God's own house!

05:59.125 --> 06:01.394
Why does God need
so many houses?

06:01.461 --> 06:03.063
Couldn't some go to poor people?

06:03.129 --> 06:05.232
You just stop right there, boy.

06:05.298 --> 06:06.566
You do not question

06:06.633 --> 06:09.269
God's real estate holdings
and tax‐free status.

06:09.336 --> 06:12.272
(exhales) I have to let off
a little steam.

06:12.339 --> 06:15.575
Shucks! Shucks! Shucks!

06:18.311 --> 06:19.579
(grunts)

06:19.646 --> 06:22.015
That's it. Young man,
I am FaceTiming the reverend.

06:23.116 --> 06:24.818
(chuckles):
Reverend,

06:24.885 --> 06:26.887
I know you hate it
when I bother you.

06:26.953 --> 06:28.221
(theme from <i>Swan Lake</i> playing)

06:28.288 --> 06:30.557
‐Aah!
‐(crying)

06:30.624 --> 06:32.158
It's okay. It's okay.

06:32.225 --> 06:34.628
I'm at my daughter's
ballet recital.

06:34.694 --> 06:35.629
Oh, is she good?

06:35.695 --> 06:38.398
Seriously, are any of them good?

06:38.465 --> 06:40.467
<i>Reverend, like the pharaoh's</i>
<i>army in the Red Sea,</i>

06:40.533 --> 06:41.635
<i>I'm in over my head.</i>

06:41.701 --> 06:43.703
<i>My heathen son</i>
<i>needs you right now.</i>

06:46.706 --> 06:47.974
Oh, sorry, got to go.

06:48.041 --> 06:49.643
I have to read the last rites...

06:49.709 --> 06:51.678
for the art of ballet.

06:51.745 --> 06:54.214
Lord, please punish
my boy thoroughly

06:54.281 --> 06:57.717
so he may once again believe
in thine divine mercy.

06:57.784 --> 07:01.254
‐Daddy, I have a problem.
‐Oh, you, too?

07:01.321 --> 07:04.958
I accidentally watched
a <i>30 Rock</i> by mistake.

07:05.025 --> 07:07.127
Oh! Oh, my good, good boy.

07:07.193 --> 07:09.429
‐Mmm.
‐So it's okay to watch?

07:09.496 --> 07:12.499
Just Kenneth. Just Kenneth. Mmm.

07:14.401 --> 07:15.635
(groans)

07:15.702 --> 07:18.505
Good morning, Rod. Todd. God.

07:18.571 --> 07:19.940
‐Good morning.
‐Morning.

07:20.006 --> 07:22.642
Let us, uh, stiffly resume
our nice, regular routine.

07:22.709 --> 07:24.811
Dear Lord, we thank you
for this breakfast,

07:24.878 --> 07:28.448
each generic brand Circle‐O
a symbol of God's unending love.

07:28.515 --> 07:30.016
‐Amen.
‐Amen.

07:30.083 --> 07:31.851
Todd?

07:33.386 --> 07:35.555
Son? Can I just get an amen?

07:36.589 --> 07:37.958
<i>A prayer without an amen</i>

07:38.024 --> 07:39.526
<i>is like a Tootsie Pop</i>
<i>without a center.</i>

07:39.592 --> 07:41.861
<i>Oh, I apologize for thinking</i>
<i>the word "tootsie."</i>

07:41.928 --> 07:43.296
<i>But there must be a way</i>

07:43.363 --> 07:45.165
<i>to scare religion back</i>
<i>into my son.</i>

07:45.231 --> 07:48.034
<i>Isn't there some hell on earth</i>
<i>I could briefly place him in?</i>

07:48.101 --> 07:49.636
HOMER:
Let me in, boy!

07:49.703 --> 07:52.205
The school bus
will be here any minute!

07:52.272 --> 07:55.342
(laughs) To find your clothes,
just solve this series of clues:

07:55.408 --> 07:57.711
what has bark but no bite?

07:57.777 --> 07:59.145
Um, the dog?

07:59.212 --> 08:01.815
‐(imitates buzzer)
Wrong. A tree.
‐(groans)

08:01.881 --> 08:03.516
Here's another.
If a plane crashes

08:03.583 --> 08:05.518
on the border
of North and South Dakota,

08:05.585 --> 08:07.620
where do you bury the survivors?

08:07.687 --> 08:08.788
Uh, Minnesota.

08:08.855 --> 08:10.357
(imitates buzzer)
Wrong.

08:10.423 --> 08:13.126
You don't bury the survivors.
They're survivors!

08:13.193 --> 08:15.128
I don't understand,
but I'll bury you.

08:15.195 --> 08:16.997
Tell you what.
I'll give you your pants back

08:17.063 --> 08:19.833
<i>‐if</i> you can answer
this last one.
‐Uh‐huh.

08:19.899 --> 08:22.035
‐What has two hairs on top...
‐Right.

08:22.102 --> 08:24.504
‐...is somebody's dad...
‐Somebody's dad, yes.

08:24.571 --> 08:27.307
...and starting right now
he's getting quite mad?

08:27.374 --> 08:30.310
I don't know,
but just give me my pants, boy!

08:31.378 --> 08:32.512
(kids laughing)

08:32.579 --> 08:34.014
(Bart laughs)

08:34.080 --> 08:35.281
Can we take pictures?

08:35.348 --> 08:37.517
Wait, you see that, too?

08:40.420 --> 08:41.688
<i>FLANDERS:</i>
<i>That Simpson house</i>

08:41.755 --> 08:43.957
<i>will put the fear of God</i>
<i>in him.</i>

08:44.024 --> 08:45.625
Give me your pants.

08:46.793 --> 08:48.962
Todd Flanders, I cast thee out.

08:49.029 --> 08:51.431
♪ <i>His little mind</i> ♪

08:51.498 --> 08:54.367
♪ <i>Is filled with doubt</i> ♪

08:54.434 --> 08:59.139
♪ <i>So now we have</i>
<i>to cast him out</i> ♪

08:59.205 --> 09:04.010
♪ <i>You'll learn</i>
<i>the Lord is sweet</i> ♪

09:04.077 --> 09:09.649
♪ <i>On his journey of 40 feet.</i> ♪

09:16.823 --> 09:19.259
Daddy, do you love me more now?

09:19.325 --> 09:20.627
(chuckles)
Just by asking,

09:20.693 --> 09:22.695
you have committed the sin
of pride.

09:24.631 --> 09:25.799
Yes, Ned, yes.

09:25.865 --> 09:27.534
We'll keep him here
till tomorrow.

09:27.600 --> 09:30.070
Yes, I'll read him
a good bedtime story.

09:30.136 --> 09:32.038
Right, right. No wizards.

09:32.105 --> 09:34.541
No pagans. No wild things.

09:34.607 --> 09:36.876
How about
<i>The Very Hungry Caterpillar?</i>

09:36.943 --> 09:38.545
No, that celebrates gluttony.

09:38.611 --> 09:40.280
<i>Clifford the Big Red Dog?</i>

09:40.346 --> 09:42.649
(scoffs) Clifford
the satanic abomination.

09:42.715 --> 09:43.783
<i>Everyone Poops?</i>

09:43.850 --> 09:45.752
Not me.

09:45.819 --> 09:47.654
Todd. Psst! Todd.

09:47.720 --> 09:50.323
I know what it's like to leave
the faith of your family.

09:50.390 --> 09:51.991
Thank you so much, Lisa.

09:52.058 --> 09:53.593
At last, someone gets it.

09:53.660 --> 09:55.495
(new age music playing)

09:55.562 --> 09:57.497
But have I got a god for you.

09:57.564 --> 09:59.833
Consider the Buddha.
He brings peace from within.

09:59.899 --> 10:01.768
He avoids the pitfalls of ego,

10:01.835 --> 10:03.837
he loves yoga <i>and</i> Yoda,

10:03.903 --> 10:05.839
and he's lost weight.

10:05.905 --> 10:07.507
What happens when you die?

10:07.574 --> 10:11.144
You get reincarnated as a human
or an animal or a ghost.

10:11.211 --> 10:15.014
Pass. Buddha's no god,
and neither is God.

10:15.081 --> 10:17.016
Don't worry, I'll get him.

10:17.083 --> 10:20.687
By the way, what did you
reincarnate David Bowie as?

10:20.753 --> 10:22.856
Help me, love. It's Bowie.

10:22.922 --> 10:26.259
(gasps)
I've been meditating too much.

10:26.326 --> 10:28.027
Where's Todd?

10:28.094 --> 10:29.529
It was horrible.

10:29.596 --> 10:31.531
I woke up,
and he'd cleaned my room.

10:31.598 --> 10:33.366
What kind of psycho does that?

10:33.433 --> 10:34.834
Hi, Grampa Simpson.

10:34.901 --> 10:36.202
(exclaiming)

10:36.269 --> 10:38.171
You're talking to me directly?

10:38.238 --> 10:40.707
Even my Alexa won't do that.

10:40.773 --> 10:42.375
<i>ELDERLY FEMALE VOICE:</i>
<i>Being with him</i>

10:42.442 --> 10:46.246
<i>has made me</i> so <i>tired.</i>

10:46.312 --> 10:47.647
<i>HOMER:</i>
<i>Hey, Marge,</i>

10:47.714 --> 10:49.082
you may have noticed

10:49.149 --> 10:51.284
I took a shower
earlier this week.

10:51.351 --> 10:52.719
(makes kissing sounds)

10:52.785 --> 10:54.220
I can't. I can't.

10:54.287 --> 10:56.055
Not with Todd in the house.

10:56.122 --> 10:58.625
Oh, we've had kids in the house
for ten years.

10:58.691 --> 11:01.361
Not that one.
He's used to silence.

11:01.427 --> 11:03.563
‐He'll hear us.
‐No, he won't.

11:03.630 --> 11:05.231
TODD:
Yes, I will!

11:05.298 --> 11:07.901
Oof! Got to get rid of that kid.

11:08.635 --> 11:09.903
Can it be?

11:09.969 --> 11:11.337
Oh, my goodness!

11:11.404 --> 11:13.173
The face of our Lord and Savior

11:13.239 --> 11:14.874
in a humble piece of toast?

11:14.941 --> 11:17.343
Clearly,
no human could have made this.

11:17.410 --> 11:18.611
Huh?

11:18.678 --> 11:20.213
And the Lord said,

11:20.280 --> 11:23.049
"Take this and eat,
for I am the toast of the town."

11:23.116 --> 11:25.218
‐You drew that on.
‐No, no.

11:25.285 --> 11:27.787
God drew it on.
Look, he signed it.

11:27.854 --> 11:29.722
"Jebus." See?

11:29.789 --> 11:32.592
Why would God make toast
that looked like Jesus?

11:32.659 --> 11:34.260
'Cause parents are always
showing off pictures

11:34.327 --> 11:37.063
‐of their kids?
‐(munching)

11:37.130 --> 11:39.065
(crying):
So much innocent bread died

11:39.132 --> 11:40.500
for my sins.

11:40.567 --> 11:42.168
(sobbing)

11:42.235 --> 11:44.604
So innocent.

11:44.671 --> 11:46.573
♪ <i>What is good</i> ♪

11:46.639 --> 11:48.508
♪ <i>And what is sin</i> ♪

11:48.575 --> 11:54.480
♪ <i>Bart wants</i>
<i>to get rid of him.</i> ♪

11:54.547 --> 11:55.815
Yo, this is Todd.

11:55.882 --> 11:58.451
I have to share my room
until he believes in God again.

11:58.518 --> 12:01.154
You don't believe in God?
Well, that's crazy.

12:01.221 --> 12:03.923
Who else but an all‐loving,
omnipotent being

12:03.990 --> 12:06.826
could create beautiful wedgies
and purple nurples?

12:06.893 --> 12:08.328
Not so fast.

12:08.394 --> 12:10.463
What if I'm the only being
in the universe,

12:10.530 --> 12:12.298
and you're all
my mental projections?

12:12.365 --> 12:14.067
Project this!

12:14.133 --> 12:17.070
I must have wanted this
to happen!

12:17.136 --> 12:19.305
So now that you see
how bad kids turn out,

12:19.372 --> 12:20.673
you want to go home, right?

12:20.740 --> 12:22.909
Stop using us as examples!

12:22.976 --> 12:25.211
I believe your friends
are all going to Hell.

12:25.278 --> 12:27.180
‐Whoa!
‐Yeah!
‐Cool!

12:27.247 --> 12:28.448
‐(Homer giggling)
‐(Marge moaning)

12:28.514 --> 12:30.283
(Homer and Marge moaning)

12:33.386 --> 12:34.787
TODD:
I hear you!

12:34.854 --> 12:36.723
What <i>doesn't</i>
that little twerp hear?

12:36.789 --> 12:39.559
TODD:
I don't know, but I heard that.

12:39.626 --> 12:41.027
(dryer rattling)

12:41.094 --> 12:42.962
(quietly):
Okay. He can't hear us now.

12:43.029 --> 12:44.564
TODD:
Yes, I can.

12:44.631 --> 12:47.066
You're unbuttoning your shirt,
Mr. Simpson.

12:48.701 --> 12:50.970
What does that paper say?

12:52.872 --> 12:55.508
LISA:
Oh. Hi, Todd.

12:55.575 --> 12:56.909
Still seeking enlightenment?

12:56.976 --> 12:58.711
I told you, not now.

12:58.778 --> 13:00.647
Maybe I'll reconsider
your stupid beliefs

13:00.713 --> 13:02.548
when I come back as a worm.

13:02.615 --> 13:05.151
In Buddhism,
that's halfway to "yes"!

13:05.218 --> 13:07.320
Look, Todd,
you don't have to believe.

13:07.387 --> 13:10.690
In church, just smile and nod,
but be sleeping on the inside.

13:10.757 --> 13:12.392
That works at work, too.

13:12.458 --> 13:14.227
But I really <i>don't</i> believe.

13:14.294 --> 13:17.530
I'm sad because my mommy's gone
and never coming back.

13:17.597 --> 13:19.232
You know how that feels?

13:19.299 --> 13:20.667
Oh, do I.

13:20.733 --> 13:22.702
Oh, no, don't relive it. Don't!

13:23.770 --> 13:25.138
You don't come home for dinner

13:25.204 --> 13:26.539
till 10:00 at night.

13:26.606 --> 13:28.308
You never cook anything
worth eating.

13:28.374 --> 13:30.209
Well, who wants
to cook for a failure?

13:30.276 --> 13:32.412
Good God, woman,
why did you marry me?

13:32.478 --> 13:34.947
To piss off my mother,
and it worked!

13:35.014 --> 13:38.117
Tell the kid I love him,
but I'm as bad at goodbyes

13:38.184 --> 13:41.754
‐as I am at picking husbands.
‐(Grampa groaning)

13:41.821 --> 13:44.791
(crying):
My mom is gone.

13:44.857 --> 13:47.060
And so is my ice cream.

13:47.126 --> 13:50.163
And so is my hair!

13:51.664 --> 13:55.001
Moe, I got to get drunk.
And fast.

13:58.104 --> 13:59.772
FLANDERS:
I'll take one, too.

13:59.839 --> 14:01.341
BOTH:
What the...?!

14:01.407 --> 14:03.476
I'm losing everything.
Just give me a drink!

14:03.543 --> 14:05.678
I'm sorry, Flanders.
I can't pour you a drink.

14:05.745 --> 14:08.581
You're too good. It's just,
it's not something I can do.

14:08.648 --> 14:10.850
Please. I'm begging you.

14:10.917 --> 14:12.919
Yeah, that's $24.

14:12.985 --> 14:17.790
♪ <i>Ned Flanders</i>
<i>is drinking today</i> ♪

14:17.857 --> 14:21.627
♪ <i>Allelujah</i> ♪

14:21.694 --> 14:26.933
♪ <i>His son Todd</i>
<i>has gone astray</i> ♪

14:26.999 --> 14:31.904
♪ <i>Allelujah</i> ♪

14:31.971 --> 14:35.308
♪ <i>Raise your mug</i>
<i>and drink it down</i> ♪

14:35.375 --> 14:40.346
♪ <i>Allelujah</i> ♪

14:40.413 --> 14:42.682
BARITONE SINGER:
♪ <i>In the worst bar</i> ♪

14:42.749 --> 14:45.184
♪ <i>In this town</i> ♪

14:45.251 --> 14:50.089
♪ <i>Allelujah.</i> ♪

14:51.424 --> 14:53.025
(slurring): You know,
Homer, I always thought

14:53.092 --> 14:54.794
you proved the existence of God.

14:54.861 --> 14:57.630
I mean, you fall off cliffs,
and you're fit as a fiddle.

14:57.697 --> 14:59.132
Well, ain't that a diddle!

14:59.198 --> 15:00.867
(laughs)

15:00.933 --> 15:02.435
‐Diddly, diddly.
‐(laughs)

15:02.502 --> 15:04.103
‐Diddle, diddle, diddle, diddle.
‐(laughs): Diddly, diddly.

15:04.170 --> 15:05.538
Whoa!

15:05.605 --> 15:07.974
(both laughing)

15:08.040 --> 15:09.976
So this is what it's like

15:10.042 --> 15:11.744
to look down on someone.

15:11.811 --> 15:13.012
(belches)

15:13.079 --> 15:14.914
You know what, Ned?
There may...

15:14.981 --> 15:16.482
there may not be a heaven,

15:16.549 --> 15:18.918
but getting drunk with you
ain't hell.

15:18.985 --> 15:21.854
(both laugh)

15:21.921 --> 15:23.322
(mumbles):
Oh, you're great.

15:23.389 --> 15:26.325
This is the beginning
of a beautiful...

15:26.392 --> 15:27.693
(grunting)

15:27.760 --> 15:29.762
You killed them!

15:29.829 --> 15:31.664
This is the worst
Uber ride ever!

15:31.731 --> 15:33.332
You're getting four stars.

15:33.399 --> 15:38.237
No...!

15:44.043 --> 15:46.045
♪ ♪

15:57.256 --> 15:59.192
Welcome to Heaven.

15:59.258 --> 16:02.195
Oh, Lord. It's just as beautiful
as I pictured it.

16:02.261 --> 16:04.330
This is your version, Ned.

16:04.397 --> 16:06.399
Homer gets his, too.

16:08.935 --> 16:11.471
So, not like I'm feeling
I put in way too much work,

16:11.537 --> 16:13.372
but Homer got in, too?

16:13.439 --> 16:16.209
Well, a couple of years ago,
sloth became a virtue.

16:16.275 --> 16:18.211
I don't really understand it.

16:18.277 --> 16:20.079
You'd have to talk to my kid.

16:20.146 --> 16:22.181
He's 33 and still lives at home.

16:22.248 --> 16:24.584
I've been through
some stuff, man.

16:24.650 --> 16:26.986
(gasps)
Abe Lincoln!

16:27.053 --> 16:28.421
Did you know the picture

16:28.488 --> 16:31.657
about my life is
Spielberg's biggest movie?

16:31.724 --> 16:35.194
No! What about <i>Jaws</i> and <i>E. T.,</i>
and all the <i>Jurassic...?</i>

16:35.261 --> 16:37.396
Well, how did I do
in the awards?

16:37.463 --> 16:39.899
‐You were beaten by <i>Argo.</i>
<i>‐Argo?!</i>

16:39.966 --> 16:43.703
That was the worst experience
I ever had in a theater.

16:43.769 --> 16:45.872
You have other people to see.

16:45.938 --> 16:48.207
‐Wear these passes.
‐Visitors?

16:48.274 --> 16:49.775
Hmm, that's odd.

16:49.842 --> 16:52.044
It must mean that
your bodies aren't dead yet.

16:52.111 --> 16:54.080
♪ <i>We need you now</i> ♪

16:54.146 --> 16:58.284
♪ <i>O God on high</i> ♪

16:58.351 --> 17:04.824
♪ <i>So stupid Flanders</i>
<i>and Homer don't die.</i> ♪

17:04.891 --> 17:07.927
Ned Flanders, I swear to you
I will use every ounce of skill

17:07.994 --> 17:10.096
in my body
to bring you back to life.

17:10.162 --> 17:12.265
(sniffles)
What about Homer?

17:12.331 --> 17:13.666
Mm, que será, será.

17:13.733 --> 17:15.067
(laughs)

17:15.134 --> 17:17.737
(sobbing)

17:21.240 --> 17:24.877
(sobbing)

17:24.944 --> 17:27.613
Oh, my.
They're holding a vigil.

17:27.680 --> 17:30.483
Look how many, many lives
Dad touched.

17:30.550 --> 17:32.118
That's Flanders' vigil.

17:32.184 --> 17:33.653
Dad's is over there.

17:33.719 --> 17:37.056
Vigils are a surprisingly
large part of this job.

17:37.123 --> 17:39.659
Oh, yeah! So sad!

17:39.725 --> 17:42.795
Dad's an acquired taste, Lis,
like Hawaiian pizza.

17:42.862 --> 17:46.165
Dad never judged a pizza
by where it came from.

17:46.232 --> 17:49.101
(cries)
He just ate it.

17:49.168 --> 17:50.970
<i>BART:</i>
<i>God, this is just you and me,</i>

17:51.037 --> 17:52.638
<i>so I'm gonna tell you a secre.</i>

17:52.705 --> 17:55.341
<i>I love my dad,</i>
<i>so please don't take him.</i>

17:55.408 --> 17:56.709
(Lisa cries)

17:56.776 --> 17:58.644
Bart, what are you praying for?

17:58.711 --> 18:00.379
New bike.

18:02.114 --> 18:04.317
Are you sure you don't want
to pray for your dad?

18:04.383 --> 18:05.818
I can't pray.

18:05.885 --> 18:08.120
I don't think
anyone's listening anymore.

18:08.187 --> 18:10.990
Oh, sweetie, prayer doesn't
have to be to God.

18:11.057 --> 18:13.459
It can also just be
an honest conversation

18:13.526 --> 18:15.428
we have with ourselves.

18:15.494 --> 18:17.897
Just do what your heart
tells you.

18:17.964 --> 18:21.567
Oh, I'm not really sure
what's happening,

18:21.634 --> 18:24.770
but I'm really sad,
and I need help.

18:24.837 --> 18:29.141
♪ <i>Rejoice, rejoice</i> ♪

18:29.208 --> 18:33.145
♪ <i>O Springfield town</i> ♪

18:33.212 --> 18:36.148
♪ <i>'Cause what goes up</i> ♪

18:36.215 --> 18:40.620
♪ <i>Must come down.</i> ♪

18:40.686 --> 18:41.887
(buzzing)

18:43.589 --> 18:45.057
(ship horn blows)

18:45.124 --> 18:46.392
(cheering)

18:46.459 --> 18:48.160
I'm winning every bet!

18:48.227 --> 18:50.563
And there's no stupid
Fox halftime show.

18:50.630 --> 18:52.565
Could Heaven be any better?

18:52.632 --> 18:54.567
(munching)

18:54.634 --> 18:57.703
I agree. This is everything
I could possibly dream of.

18:57.770 --> 18:59.538
(plays pretty chord)

18:59.605 --> 19:00.640
(gasps)

19:00.706 --> 19:03.142
Todd is praying.
He's praying for me.

19:03.209 --> 19:05.311
(laughs)
And it's working!

19:05.378 --> 19:07.179
I'm returning to my family!

19:07.246 --> 19:08.681
Bye, Homer.

19:11.417 --> 19:13.185
‐Homer?
‐Mom?

19:13.252 --> 19:17.790
I never got a chance
to say goodbye, but now I can.

19:17.857 --> 19:19.692
Remember, I'm not a hugger.

19:19.759 --> 19:21.127
Oh, right. Sorry.

19:21.193 --> 19:23.529
You never need
to apologize to me.

19:23.596 --> 19:26.365
In my eyes, you're perfect.

19:26.432 --> 19:28.200
Ah, we're in Heaven.

19:28.267 --> 19:30.036
Come here, you.

19:30.102 --> 19:34.674
Oh, my God,
this is all I ever wanted!

19:34.740 --> 19:35.908
<i>HOMER:</i>
<i>Aw, damn it!</i>

19:37.743 --> 19:40.579
Hallelujah! I'm alive and back
in this big beautiful world.

19:40.646 --> 19:43.115
I could kiss
the first thing I see.

19:43.182 --> 19:45.284
Ah. Promise is a promise.

19:45.351 --> 19:46.686
‐Homie!
‐Dad!

19:46.752 --> 19:48.454
‐Doughboy!
‐Yay!

19:48.521 --> 19:51.624
Daddy, you came back!
I believe again!

19:51.691 --> 19:53.959
Two lives saved by prayer.

19:54.026 --> 19:55.461
And modern medicine.

19:55.528 --> 19:57.263
This is why I became a doctor.

19:57.329 --> 19:59.231
Because you both owe me $12,000.

19:59.298 --> 20:00.633
(laughs)

20:05.271 --> 20:06.806
No, no, no, no.

20:06.872 --> 20:08.641
Nirvana is for closers,
and you couldn't close the deal.

20:08.708 --> 20:10.609
‐But‐but...
‐But‐but‐but‐but‐but nothing!

20:10.676 --> 20:13.279
You couldn't even close
Todd frickin' Flanders!

20:13.345 --> 20:15.181
That kid would follow
a butterfly.

20:15.247 --> 20:17.116
Just give me one more chance.

20:17.183 --> 20:20.820
Do you think I got
to be Buddha by being patient?!

20:20.886 --> 20:23.856
Check this out.
I got you Ralph Wiggum.

20:23.923 --> 20:27.193
Ralph Wiggum? What am I gonna do
with Ralph Wiggum?

20:27.259 --> 20:29.495
Everything is nothing!

20:29.562 --> 20:32.998
Kid, you just blew my mind.

20:33.065 --> 20:35.668
(organ music playing)

20:41.741 --> 20:43.375
Good night, Roddy.

20:47.113 --> 20:49.081
Ha!

20:49.148 --> 20:55.421
♪ <i>Praise God from whom</i>
<i>all blessings flow</i> ♪

20:55.488 --> 20:56.889
♪ <i>Praise God</i> ♪

20:56.956 --> 21:02.294
♪ <i>It's almost time to go</i> ♪

21:02.361 --> 21:08.601
♪ <i>Todd has found</i>
<i>just what he seeks</i> ♪

21:08.667 --> 21:15.074
♪ <i>New episode in two weeks.</i> ♪

21:21.647 --> 21:24.483
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH

21:30.256 --> 21:31.757
Shh!
